thread.title: Zimbabwe official: Country not extraditing dentist who killed Cecil
thread.title_full: Zimbabwe official: Country not extraditing dentist who killed Cecil - Chicago Tribune

author: Tribune wire reports
title: Zimbabwe official: Country not extraditing dentist who killed Cecil
text:
Zimbabwe is not interested in extraditing American who killed Cecil the lion, said a cabinet minister.
American dentist Walter James Palmer shot the well-known lion in July. Charges have not been filed against Palmer, according to prosecutors, while in Minnesota the dentist has reopened his practice.Zimbabwe has charged a man on whose land Cecil was shot.
Zimbabwe's environment, water and climate minister Oppah Muchinguri said in July that Palmer should be extradited for killing the lion. But the National Prosecuting Authority, which handles extradition requests, said on Tuesday police have not supplied the required documentation. Police declined to comment on possible charges against Palmer.
Zimbabwe tightened regulations for lion, elephant and leopard hunting after the killing of Cecil, a lion well known by tourists and who was being studied by scientists.
Theo Bronkhorst, a professional hunter who helped Palmer, has been charged with "failure to prevent an illegal hunt."
Associated Press
 Africa
